Cary's Potato Kugel

3 large baking potatoes
1 onion
2 eggs, lightly beaten
1/2 cup flour
3/4 tsp. salt
1/2 tsp. pepper
3 tbsp. margarine

1. Preheat the oven to 375 degrees.
2. Peel and coarsely grate the potatoes. Place the potato in a cheese cloth and squeeze out as much moisture as possible.
3. Finely chop the onions in a food processor and add them (including all the onion juice) to the grated potatoes in a large mixing bowl.
4. Add the eggs, flour, salt and pepper and with a spoon until all ingredients are distributed.
5. Melt the margarine in a 9x9 baking pan, then pour in the potato mixture and smooth it out with a fork until the surface is even.
6. Bake for 50 minutes.



